Most of the pictures that I see that are "ghosts" are classic cases of 
Pareidolia. Its something that we all have and it stems from when we were 
babies. Our brains naturally subconsciously make out faces so we can 
recognize a parent or family member after we are born. Thats why babies 
naturally know to look at your face, into your eyes and they don't stare at 
your feet. When we get older it still stays with us. Thats why sometimes we 
see faces on clouds, bushes, random patterns, fronts of houses, cars etc.. 
Even shadows, lights, reflections smudges on windows and photos we easily 
work out faces and bodies. The second photo is clearly a developing fault 
but the others are classic (coincidence / pareidolia.)  and not demons and 
ghosts. Literally billions of pictures are taken every day.. its going to 
happen to a small percentage of them. Also, I'm not saying that ghosts do 
not exist.. Like everyone else on this planet I simply do not know.  ﻿
